Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Quarter @lime{1}.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in scallion whites; cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @water{1/2%cup}, @Tex-Mex paste{1}, @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, and juice from half the lime until thoroughly combined. Bring to a simmer and cook until sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

While chicken cooks, partially open @microwaveable jasmine rice{1} package; microwave according to package instructions, ~{90%seconds}.

Stir @butter{1%tablespoon} into pan with chicken mixture until melted. Sprinkle with @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup}, then cover pan until cheese melts, ~{1%minute}.

Massage rice in package, then divide between #bowls{}. Spoon cheesy chicken on top. Dollop with @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.